The article discusses the issue of inflation and its impact on the economy. The author highlights the need to address inflation, particularly the increase in gas prices due to the conflict in Ukraine. The author calls for urgent action from both the administration and Congress to lower prices for the American people. They suggest passing a bill to cut shipping costs, legislation to reduce energy bills and prescription drug costs, and implementing tax reform to make the wealthiest Americans and big corporations pay their fair share. The author emphasizes the importance of addressing inflation and opposes any plan to raise taxes on the middle class and working families.